docs.abstract: The presidential race entered extraordinary new ground as the leading Democrats called off primary-night events in Cleveland, and President Trump’s signature rallies also faced an uncertain future.
docs.snippet: The presidential race entered extraordinary new ground as the leading Democrats called off primary-night events in Cleveland, and President Trump’s signature rallies also faced an uncertain future.
docs.lead_paragraph: The nation’s presidential race entered an unpredictable new phase on Tuesday after the two leading Democratic candidates canceled big primary-night campaign events because of worries about the coronavirus, and Vice President Mike Pence said that the future of President Trump’s signature rallies would be decided on a “a day-to-day basis.”

headline.main: Sanders and Biden Cancel Events as Coronavirus Fears Upend Primary
headline.print_headline: How Concerns  Of Coronavirus  May Alter Race

byline.original: By Sydney Ember, Annie Karni and Maggie Haberman

docs.abstract: He has such a thorough hold on the party now that any collapse would probably require a political U-turn as sharp as the one that precipitated his rise.

docs.lead_paragraph: The state of our union is unsettled, chaotic, impossible to pin down. The state of the Democratic primary, improbably, is not.

docs.abstract: Older voters have easily carried Mr. Biden to victory in multiple primaries. But if he wants to beat President Trump, he will have to win younger voters too — and that may not be easy.
